# One proxy per line. Lines starting with # or empty lines are ignored.
# Rename this file to `proxy.txt` (no `.example`) and the scraper will
# pick it up automatically. Alternative: set the SCRAPER_PROXIES env var
# (comma- or newline-separated, same formats).
#
# Supported formats:
#
#   host:port
#   host:port:user:pass
#   user:pass@host:port
#   http://user:pass@host:port
#   https://user:pass@host:port
#
# Each proxy in the pool gets its own browser session (own cookie jar,
# own bootstrap state). The scraper round-robins requests across the
# pool and skips any proxy that returns 3 consecutive failures for 60s.

# Example entries — replace with real proxies:
# 1.2.3.4:8080
# 1.2.3.4:8080:myuser:mypass
# myuser:mypass@1.2.3.4:8080
